cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

The paper proposes a new representation learning method that incorporates a structure regularization term into the loss function of the deep learning pipeline. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SD). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories as the paper focuses on representation learning and its applications in digit recognition, image classification, and object tracking.
